Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Init", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7873010974064755`*^9, 
  3.787301099609595*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"08806a5f-1410-4b58-9789-\
0f1470c472af"],

Cell["\<\
The SpaceSpinors package is designed to handle 3 dimensional space spinors on \
spacelike hypersurfaces in a 4 dimensional spacetime. \[LineSeparator]These \
were introduced by Sommers (1980), and Sen (1981). See also Torres del \
Castillo (2003), B\[ADoubleDot]ckdahl and Valiente Kroon (2010), and the book \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Conformal Methods in General Relativity\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] Chapter 4 by Valiente Kroon.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.959698643306385*^9, 3.9596986551407967`*^9}, {
  3.9596988571765957`*^9, 3.959698860137247*^9}, {3.959698907201456*^9, 
  3.95969898603603*^9}, {3.959699033944809*^9, 3.9596991060648136`*^9}, {
  3.9596991484255085`*^9, 
  3.959699257073017*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d46894a4-a054-ae45-a4e7-\
e7c100cbbf2b"],

Cell["\<\
The current version of the package is incomplete and should be seen as \
experimental. Names of functions and variables can change in later versions. \
The implementation is currently focused on the index-free notation of the \
SymSpin package. Many tools for handling the indexed versions are not \
implemented yet. Tools for translation between spinor and tensor notation is \
also underdeveloped.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.959699258210972*^9, 3.959699303603529*^9}, {
  3.959699361608238*^9, 3.9596994923681145`*^9}, {3.9597001301674747`*^9, 
  3.959700180001545*^9}, {3.959700261938387*^9, 
  3.959700292111521*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9f925528-f3dc-b949-99c9-\
f525f26c13d3"],

